{          Finding a 4-4 Major Fit          }
^-|fp||cp|8|AT|^B@2^Y@3^*BHoward: ^*N|cp||at|As mentioned above, responder's most important objective is to find a major suit fit. Therefore, if responder has a 4-card major, it should be bid. With both 4 hearts and 4 spades, responder should bid hearts. When partner opens 1C, some players will bid 1D with 4+ diamonds and a 4-card major; however, the modern tendency is to bypass the diamond suit and bid 1 of the major.|
