NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*BHoward: ^*N|cp||at|Therefore, you have to decide whether or not to bypass diamonds. More people do these days. BTW, for you bridge nerds, that treatment of bypassing diamonds is known as "Walsh." Now, let me tell you the approach I use. If I have a hand good enough for a |CP|8|AT|^*Usecond bid^*N |CP||AT|over 1N by opener's rebid, I will bid diamonds rather than bypassing them. Here, since North has only 8 points, I would bid 1H with this hand. Further, the rule is with two 4-card majors, you bid hearts first. That gives opener, who often has spades, a chance to bid spades. |
